PN,38202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1781524080
OL,3,CHeatwave possible across Southern
OL,4,CEngland as 'warm plume' moves towards
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FWhilst today (Monday 15 June) is
OL,8,Fexpected to be dry and settled, but
OL,9,Fcloudy and cooler in the North East
OL,10,Fwith a chance of showers and
OL,11,Fthunderstorms.
OL,13,FFurther cloud and rain could spread
OL,14,Ffrom the west on Tuesday.
OL,16,FMet Office meteorologist Honor
OL,17,FCriswick said high pressure building
OL,18,Facross the country will bring warm and
OL,19,Fhumid conditions, with temperatures
OL,20,Fclimbing above the seasonal average in
OL,21,Fsome areas.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1781524080
OL,3,CHeatwave possible across Southern
OL,4,CEngland as 'warm plume' moves towards
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FShe told the Press Association:
OL,8,F"Throughout the week things are
OL,9,Fheating up in the south and South East.
OL,11,F"We've got high pressure starting to
OL,12,Fbuild and there's a warm plume moving
OL,13,Fup through continental Europe.
OL,15,F"Whether or not it'll be a heatwave
OL,16,Fremains to be seen as there's still a
OL,17,Flot to play for, but things are
OL,18,Fcertainly turning a lot warmer, if not
OL,19,Fmaybe even hot, by the end of the
OL,20,Fweek, although this is mostly confined
OL,21,Fto the South East.
OL,26,@pD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
